Hey hey! I’ve got a few fun announcements!First of all: I’ll be doing a new weekly segment called “Taylor Time”… I’m sorry for those of you who are not Taylor Swift fans but as you probably know, I am a big one! Hopefully you will stick around for some covers anyway ☺️. So what this means is- I will post a poll on my story at the beginning of the week with 3 songs from one of her albums and you guy will tell me which one you would like to hear! I’ll then record and post that video. I’ll be doing this for each of her album’s start to finish! 

Next: I’ve got some new music in the works! Lots of hard work and studio time from an amazing team that I cannot wait to share with you. Thank you for your patience as I try to balance medical school and music and just life in general. I will also be updating my schedule for some summer shows soon. 

With the most love and gratitude, 
Nat 💕

To say that the year 2023 was humbling would be the understatement of the century. I failed, I learned, I loved, I lost… there were a lot of tears and a lot of smiles, but I would do it all over again if I knew I would be where I am right now. I am so incredibly blessed to have the most amazing family and friends, to be finishing up interviews for my residency in emergency medicine, to get to play music several times a week with my best friends and to have met the most amazing man on earth (@kevinhorne92). Thank you to everyone for their continued patience and support. God knows I need it. Here’s to happiness, love and positivity in 2024 🤍🎉
